-- Mexican Stock Movers: Grupo Elektra and OHL Mexico Were Active
-- B y   J o n a t h a n   J .   L e v i n
-- 2012-05-24T22:33:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-24/mexican-stock-movers-grupo-elektra-and-ohl-mexico-are-active.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Mexico City. Stock symbols are in parentheses,
and prices are as of the close of trading.  The  IPC index  climbed 0.3 percent to 37,553.21.  Grupo Elektra SA (ELEKTRA*)  , the retail and banking
company controlled by billionaire  Ricardo Salinas , tumbled 4.2
percent to 523.15 pesos. MSCI Inc. will remove Elektra from its
indexes effective May 31, according to a statement posted May 15
on its website. Shares are down 19 percent since the
announcement.  OHL Mexico SAB (OHLMEX*)  , the Mexican unit of Spanish
construction company Obrascon Huarte Lain SA, dropped 0.1
percent to 15.12 pesos. The shares rallied earlier as much as
2.1 percent as Scotia Capital analyst Marcos Duran y Casahonda
raised the company to the equivalent of hold from the equivalent
of sell. A research note e-mailed today said the revocation of a
concession in Puebla state was probably an “isolated event.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jonathan J. Levin in Mexico City at 
